    "body": "### Problem\n\nSee repro steps\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean -c \"lua require 'vim._extui'.enable { msg = { pos = 'box' } }\"`\n2. Press `qq`. The text `recording @q` is shown in cmdline\n3. Try to type an Ex command, for example `:echo \"Hello world\"`\n=> The commandline doesn't show up, instead the text `recording @q` is still in cmdline\n4. Press Enter. The text `\"Hello world\"` is shown in message window. So I can type a command to cmdline, I just cannot see it\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nLike tradition message grid, while I'm recording a macro:\n- When I go to cmdline, the text `Recording @q` should disappear, cmdline should show up\n- When I leave cmdline, the text `Recording @q` should reappear\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1fb0126a08\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot Vim feature\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nKubuntu 24.04.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKonsole 23.08.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nFrom source",
